folder: Denman Street & Elmhurst Avenue, Queens, NY
text:
Denman Street (foreground), south side, east of Elmhurst Ave., showing at the right foreground the A. Gorsline farmhouse from 1852-1860 ? - to his estate from 1873 to 1891. It was the property of the American Democratic Club in 1924.
March 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Elmhurst Avenue & Denman Street., Queens, NY
text:
Elmhurst Avenue, east side, between Denman and Elbertson Streets, showing several old dwellings, the center one of which is the A. Gorsline house. It appears on J. Riker Jr's 1852 Map of Newtown. It later became the American Democratic club.  View 2 shows a closeup of the Gorsline house.

View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster  August,1923
View 2: P. L. Sperr  November 5, 1936
